      "finalMessagePreview": "Updated the worker startup contract so a missing `assigned_bead_id` now explicitly returns `[NOOP]` or `[BLOCKED]` and asks the orchestrator for assignment, instead of self-selecting a bead.\n\nChanged:\n- [`plugins/khuym/skills/executing/SKILL.md`](./plugins/khuym/skills/executing/SKILL.md:94) now says missing/empty `assigned_bead_id` must not self-select and must ask the orchestrator for one.\n- [`plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/references/worker-template.md`](./plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/references/worker-template.md:45) now hard-stops startup when `<ASSIGNED_BEAD_ID>` is missing or empty.\n- [`plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/references/message-templates.md`](./plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/references/message-templates.md:98) now tells a worker to ask the orchestrator to assign a bead.\n- [`plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/SKILL.md`](./plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/SKILL.md:123) now marks `assigned_bead_id` as mandatory for a real worker run.\n- [`plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/tests/worker-assignment-contract.test.mjs`](./plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/tests/worker-assignment-contract.test.mjs:13) adds a regression test that checks the documented contract across the skill, template, and message formats.\n\nVerification:\n- `node --test plugins/khuym/skills/swarming/tests/worker-assignment-contract.test.mjs`\n\nI couldn’t use `br` in this environment because the local wrapper couldn’t locate the real binary, so I verified this with the focused Node test instead.",
